{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Rows with missing required fields are rejected and appear in the dead-letter queue with the original row number.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure mode is at a module handoff: CSV row parsing/indexing -> schema validation -> DLQ writer payload. A unit test of only the validator would miss row-number propagation bugs. Integration with in-process wiring and a fake/in-memory DLQ is sufficient. Rejected higher level System because behavior text does not require real S3/network/OS primitives; it only specifies rejection and DLQ contents.","test_description":"Run pipeline components together on a small CSV fixture with known missing required fields at specific line numbers. Assert invalid rows are emitted to DLQ records containing the exact original row number and that valid rows continue. Use in-process fakes for external services; no real network/subprocess.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The transformation correctly converts date strings in multiple formats (ISO 8601, US, European) to a single canonical format.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is pure transformation logic (format parsing/normalization) and can fail entirely within one function/object boundary. No module interaction is required to expose the core bug. Rejected Integration because behavior text focuses only conversion correctness, not cross-module state handoff.","test_description":"Table-driven unit test for date-normalization function with ISO 8601, US, and European inputs (plus edge cases like ambiguous dates) asserting one canonical output format.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A CSV file with 500,000 rows completes processing within the configured timeout without running out of memory.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is a real resource/performance boundary (heap growth, GC behavior, wall-clock timeout) that depends on process/runtime and OS conditions. In-process mocks cannot faithfully reproduce memory pressure and timeout behavior, so lower levels can hide failures.","test_description":"Execute the real pipeline process on a generated 500k-row CSV under production-like timeout/memory limits. Measure peak memory and total duration, and fail if OOM occurs or timeout is exceeded.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.14,"System":0.83,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the S3 bucket returns a transient 503 error, the pipeline retries with exponential backoff rather than failing the entire batch.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Primary risk is retry orchestration across pipeline + S3 client adapter + backoff policy. This can be caught with module wiring and deterministic error injection. Rejected System because behavior text is about retry policy on a 503 response, which can be reproduced with a stubbed adapter/fake clock without real network infrastructure.","test_description":"Integration test wires pipeline to an S3 adapter stub that returns 503 for first N attempts then success. Assert exponential backoff schedule (using controllable clock), retry count, and batch completion without global failure.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.19,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Rows successfully written to PostgreSQL are not duplicated if the pipeline is restarted mid-batch.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is at state handoff between batch progress tracking and database write/idempotency semantics across a restart boundary. Requires multiple modules plus a real/local DB behavior surface. Integration (with local PostgreSQL) is sufficient; System is not strictly required if restart is simulated by re-instantiating components against persisted state. Rejected higher Workflow/Agentic because no AI steps exist.","test_description":"Use a local PostgreSQL instance and run half-batch ingest, persist checkpoint/offset, simulate restart by creating a new pipeline instance, then continue. Assert final row count equals unique input rows and no duplicate keys/records exist.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.16,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}}]}
